# ROS2 DevKit

Curated Codex skills for ROS2 development.

## CLI

Install the CLI as a machine-level command outside any project virtualenv, then
configure it to use the ROS2 skills installed for your agent account.

```bash
python3 -m pip install .
scripts/configure_ros_devkit.sh --agent codex
```

Supported agent roots:

- `codex`: `~/.codex/skills/ros2`
- `claude`: `~/.claude/skills/ros2`
- `pi`: `~/.pi/agent/skills/ros2`

For another location:

```bash
scripts/configure_ros_devkit.sh --agent custom --skill-root /path/to/skills/ros2
```

The v1 command registry exposes:

```bash
ros-devkit description-scaffold --verify
ros-devkit description-scaffold --split
ros-devkit description-scaffold --create my_robot
ros-devkit doctor
```

`ros-devkit` only dispatches to scripts under the configured installed ROS2
skill root. It does not fall back to this repository's `skills/.curated/ros2`
directory.
